@node intro "Introduction & Features"

    We (I and Zeus) were thinking new ideas for doors. Then we decided to
    make a who-door that lets every user select the layout design (s)he likes
    most. Later by suggestion from Mad Jack, I added possiblity to set
    default layout design for all users. Also if user has chosen his/her
    layout, the new one defined by sysop is used. In this release there are
    included designs from Zeus, Stezotehic, Soxious, Allah and two
    ones made by Loop. Very much thanks to these dudes! Also design of
    internal /X who is included. Permission has not been asked, but I hope
    /X developers do not care about some lines..

    If sysop lets users to specify their designs, ImageView creates
    DayDream:Users/<usernum>/ImageView.DAT for information whose design
    (s)he selected. If user doesn't already have the user directory, it will
    be created.

@endnode

@node install "Installing ImageView"

Installation
~~~~~~~~~~~~
    Add something like this to ExternalCommands.DAT:

    DOOR_COMMAND.. WHO
    DOOR_TYPE..... 1
    DOOR_SECURITY. 5
    DOOR_EXECUTE.. Doors:ImageView %N
    DOOR_CONFS1... XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
    DOOR_CONFS2... XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

    ... And there is it! Compile configfile using DreamConfig, and look the
    @{"configuration" link config} chapter.

@endnode

@node config "Configuration"

    If you want to specify a design for EVERY user, create ImageView.CFG in
    your configdirectory (specified in ENV:DreamUtils). The file should contain
    only one number on the first line, where the number indicates the design
    number to use.

    1 - Zeus
    2 - Loop (first)
    3 - Loop (another one)
    4 - Stz
    5 - Soxious
    6 - Allah
    7 - Internal /X

    You can have comments at the next lines, only line 1 is used by IV.

    Note that if you specify the design there and user has selected already
    his/her design, sysop defined design will be used, but the user's
    personal "configfile", is not removed. (If you delete the configfile in
    ENV:DreamUtils, user's own selection will take place again)

@endnode

@node history "History"

  v1.0    First public release - bugraports welcome!
  v1.1    If user was using design by Soxious and the next node(s) after
          his/her node were inactive or waiting for a call, his/her location
          was displayed at the other nodes also. Fixed.
          Added design by Presence.
  v1.2    Added design by Allah, permission for logo has been asked from HJ.
          If you give number of outlook at the commandline, it overrides
          all other selections. For example WHO 4 will show node status
          using design by Stz. This is useful if you want to use specified
          design for example in Welcome.TXT/GFX. Idea by Allah, thx!
  v1.3    Added design of /X internal who. Removed design by Presence (I
          don't comment reason =). Zeus made new outlook for design selection
          and wanted that I change it, so I did it.

          Compiled now using SAS/C v6.57.

          Fixed crashes with Soxius's design. A string was 1 character longer
          than space allocated for it. :)

          In layoutselection-menu currently selected design has * in front of
          it. This makes selecting possible when not using ANSI colors.

          Sorry, I'm not sure if v1.3 has been already released. At least I
          feel like I released it, but I could not find it anywhere on my
          HD, I also searched it from some boards. So this is the version 1.3.

@endnode

